<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">When betrayed, do not leave the fellowship of your brothers in Christ.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">We should bring these feelings to them and go to God in prayer.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Pulling away from the church or fellow followers of Christ is the worst thing you can do. (Take it from me)</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Labelling all people of the kind you were betrayed by is just stoking the flames. Thinking things like &quot;All Christians are hypocrites, all men are evil, all women do is deceive&quot;, etc is not a way to move forward.</li></ul></body></html>